# Use the Makefile for project commands

Canonical command reference: **`AGENTS.md`**. This rule reinforces it for Cursor.

This repo’s workflows are wired in the root **`Makefile`**. **Always prefer `make …` targets** from the repo root for:

- **Dev servers** — `make frontend-run`, `make backend-run`
- **Tests** — `make test`, `make frontend-test`, `make backend-test`
- **Lint, types, and quality gates** — `make check` (alias `make code-quality`)
- **Fallow** — `make frontend-fallow-audit`, `make frontend-fallow-health`, `make frontend-fallow`
- **Installs and builds** — `make install`, `make frontend-install`, `make frontend-build`

Do **not** default to `cd frontend && npm …`, `cd backend && uv run …`, or `npx fallow …` when a Makefile target exists. Use ad-hoc package-manager commands only when the user explicitly asks to debug a single command, or when no `make` target covers the task yet (add a target first).

When suggesting verification after changes, cite the matching **`make …`** target and run it from the repo root.

## Frontend (SvelteKit in `frontend/`)

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Install deps | `make frontend-install` |
| Dev server | `make frontend-run` |
| Tests only | `make frontend-test` |
| Typecheck + lint + fallow audit + tests | `make frontend-check` |
| Fallow audit only (changed files) | `make frontend-fallow-audit` |
| Fallow health + letter grade | `make frontend-fallow-health` |
| Full Fallow report (whole frontend) | `make frontend-fallow` |
| Production build | `make frontend-build` |

## Backend (`backend/`)

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Install | `make backend-install` |
| Dev server | `make backend-run` |
| Tests | `make backend-test` |
| Lint + types + tests | `make backend-check` |

## Whole repo

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Install everything | `make install` |
| All tests | `make test` |
| All lint + types + fallow audit + tests | `make code-quality` (alias: `make check`) |
| Git hooks (Husky) | `make root-install` (also runs via `make install`) |

Pre-commit runs **`make code-quality`** automatically.
